
PHP SETUP 
1) Install XAMPP (https://www.apachefriends.org)
2) Enable PostgreSQL on XAMPP:
    Go to PathToXampp/xampp/php/php.ini and open the file
    Find the line which contains ";extension=php_pgsql.dll" and uncomment it (remove semi-colon)
    If there is still a problem, find the line which contains ";extension=php_pdo_pgsql.dll" and uncomment it
3) Install GhostScript (http://ghostscript.com/download/, then take the first one)
4) Install ImageMagick:
    Take ImageMagick-6.7.7-5-Q16-windows-dll (available here:http://ftp.sunet.se/pub/multimedia/graphics/ImageMagick/binaries/)
    Install it in a directory with no spaces in the name
    Download Imagick DLL: PHP5.5.x version from http://www.peewit.fr/imagick/
    Copy this DLL to xampp/php/ext
    In the php.ini file, add the line: extension=php_imagick.dll